# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __le__, __gt__, __ge__ across all 5 pathlib subjects
#
# 5 classes x 3 methods = 15 rows.
# pathlib.PurePath: __le__ = true, __gt__ = true, __ge__ = true.
# This true/true/true pattern is the key finding of wave 676 for pathlib:
# PurePath defines the full set of upper-bound ordering protocols in its
# own __dict__, enabling use in sorted containers and range comparisons.
# All subclasses (PurePosixPath, PureWindowsPath, Path, PosixPath) inherit
# these from PurePath and are false for all three in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

